Example Execution
Input 1
string s = "(()))())(";
cout << maxLength(s);  
Execution Steps
'(' at 0 â†’ push onto stack
'(' at 1 â†’ push onto stack
')' at 2 â†’ match with '(' at 1, dp[2] = 2
')' at 3 â†’ match with '(' at 0, dp[3] = dp[2] + 4 = 4
')' at 4 â†’ no matching '(', ignore
'(' at 5 â†’ push onto stack
')' at 6 â†’ match with '(' at 5, dp[6] = 2
')' at 7 â†’ no matching '(', ignore
'(' at 8 â†’ push onto stack
Final DP Array
dp = [0, 0, 2, 4, 0, 0, 2, 0, 0]
Output
4
Conclusion
Efficiently finds the longest valid parentheses substring in 
ğ‘‚
